1.How to add remote repository in vs code step by step

git init   
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git   
git remote -v   ##Verify the remote
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main   


2.If face issue in above use this-- Git conflict not able to add remote and push into main

git pull --rebase origin main   # fetch remote commits and put your local commits on top
git push -u origin main        # push after integrating (set upstream first time)
# if there are conflicts: resolve files, then run `git rebase --continue` and push
